Package: BVS.DAdj
Title: Bayesian Variable Selection with Dual-Adjacency Network-Informed Ising Priors
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Yubing Yao [aut, cre], Mahlet Tadesse [aut], Raji Balasubramanian [aut]
Maintainer: Yubing Yao <yyao@umass.edu>
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yubing", "Yao", email = "yyao@umass.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Mahlet", "Tadesse", email = "mgt26@georgetown.edu",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Raji", "Balasubramanian", email = "rbalasub@schoolph.umass.edu",
           role = "aut"))
Description: MCMC methods for Bayesian variable selection with Ising/MRF priors
    informed by graphical model adjacency. The Metropolis-Hastings sampler
    supports binary logistic outcomes, continuous Gaussian outcomes,
    right-censored time-to-event outcomes via Cox partial likelihood, and
    overdispersed count outcomes via a negative-binomial (Poisson-Gamma)
    representation; the Polya-Gamma sampler targets binary logistic outcomes.
    Supports fixed, graphical lasso, and Bayesian GGM adjacency structures
    with dense and sparse high-dimensional variants under single and dual
    network priors. Allows additional covariates (z_dat) with coefficients
    (tau) that are always included in the model and not subject to variable
    selection.
